		<title>Math Typesetting</title>
		<published>2021-05-03T09:19:42+00:00</published>
		<updated>2021-05-03T09:19:42+00:00</updated>
		<link href="https://kiyanchuk.com/math-typesetting/" type="text/html"/>
		<id>https://kiyanchuk.com/math-typesetting/</id>
		<content type="html">&lt;p&gt;Mathematical notation in a project can be enabled by using third party JavaScript libraries.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;span id=&quot;continue-reading&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this example we will be using &lt;a href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;katex.org&#x2F;&quot;&gt;KaTeX&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create a template under &lt;code&gt;&#x2F;template&#x2F;katex.html&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Within this template use the reference of &lt;a href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;katex.org&#x2F;docs&#x2F;autorender.html&quot;&gt;Auto-render Extension&lt;&#x2F;a&gt; or host these scripts locally.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inlcude the template in your page templates like so: &lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
&lt;pre data-lang=&quot;bash&quot; style=&quot;background-color:#ffffff;color:#4d4d4c;&quot; class=&quot;language-bash &quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-bash&quot; data-lang=&quot;bash&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#c82829;&quot;&gt;{%&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#4271ae;&quot;&gt; if page.extra.katex or section.extra.katex or config.extra.katex %&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#c82829;&quot;&gt;{%&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#4271ae;&quot;&gt; include &lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#718c00;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;katex.html&amp;#39; &lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#4271ae;&quot;&gt;%&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#c82829;&quot;&gt;{%&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#4271ae;&quot;&gt; endif %&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;&lt;&#x2F;pre&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To enable KaTex globally set the parameter &lt;code&gt;extra.katex&lt;&#x2F;code&gt; to &lt;code&gt;true&lt;&#x2F;code&gt; in a project’s configuration&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To enable KaTex on a per page basis include the parameter &lt;code&gt;extra.katex = true&lt;&#x2F;code&gt; in content files&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Note:&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt; &lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use the online reference of &lt;a href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;katex.org&#x2F;docs&#x2F;supported.html&quot;&gt;Supported TeX Functions&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;examples&quot;&gt;Examples&lt;&#x2F;h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Inline math: \(\varphi = \dfrac{1+\sqrt5}{2}= 1.6180339887…\) 
&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Block math:
$$
\varphi = 1+\frac{1} {1+\frac{1} {1+\frac{1} {1+\cdots} } } 
$$&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
